00:50:31.400 --> 00:50:32.090
NATALIE STARKEY: Exactly.

00:50:32.090 --> 00:50:32.660
The latter.

00:50:32.660 --> 00:50:35.240
So we think-- so I'll just
backtrack a little bit.

00:50:35.240 --> 00:50:38.420
So this object came
through our solar system.

00:50:38.420 --> 00:50:40.370
We actually think now
it was probably a comet,

00:50:40.370 --> 00:50:41.450
but we're not 100% sure.

00:50:41.450 --> 00:50:43.825
We weren't able to measure it
very well because we didn't

00:50:43.825 --> 00:50:46.160
know it was coming, but so
it wasn't on the normal orbit

00:50:46.160 --> 00:50:48.380
that all the other comets and
asteroids and planets are on.

00:50:48.380 --> 00:50:50.713
It just literally came zipping
through our solar system.

00:50:50.713 --> 00:50:52.400
It was so fast
