00:51:33.150 --> 00:51:34.650
We'd learn about
that star system

00:51:34.650 --> 00:51:37.530
that it came from, which could
be completely different to what

00:51:37.530 --> 00:51:38.280
we're seeing here.

00:51:38.280 --> 00:51:39.595
Probably would be.

00:51:39.595 --> 00:51:40.470
It could be the same.

00:51:40.470 --> 00:51:40.920
Who knows?

00:51:40.920 --> 00:51:42.270
But we know it came
from somewhere else.

00:51:42.270 --> 00:51:44.145
And we just haven't seen
one of these before.

00:51:44.145 --> 00:51:46.050
I think probably other
objects like that

00:51:46.050 --> 00:51:47.610
have gone through
the solar system,

00:51:47.610 --> 00:51:48.980
but we haven't spotted them.

00:51:48.980 --> 00:51:49.920
They go very fast.

00:51:49.920 --> 00:51:52.470
I think it was just chance
that it was seen as well.

00:51:52.470 --> 00:51:53.810
But it is fascinating.

00:51:53.810 --> 00:51:56.020
And I would love to have
some sample of that comet.

00:51:56.020 --> 00:51:58.270
It would be so cool to analyze.

00:51:58.270 --> 00:52:00.259
But yeah, I'm hoping--
you know, in the future

00:52:00.259 --> 00:52:02.550
as we get better at seeing
these things coming-- again,

00:52:02.550 --> 00:52:03.494
it wasn't very big.

00:52:03.494 --> 00:52:04.910
It was also really
weirdly shaped.

00:52:04.910 --> 00:52:07.334
It was like a cigar shape,
really long and kind of

00:52:07.334 --> 00:52:09.375
like-- you know, maybe
it's some alien spaceship.

00:52:09.375 --> 00:52:10.614
Who knows?

