But equally, some of the really
exciting scientific things

00:52:51.025 --> 00:52:52.900
happening right now are
Enceladus and Europa.

00:52:52.900 --> 00:52:54.400
Now this isn't
comets and asteroids,

00:52:54.400 --> 00:52:57.370
but this is potentially finding
life in our solar system.

00:52:57.370 --> 00:52:59.520
These are moons of
Jupiter and Saturn

00:52:59.520 --> 00:53:03.162
and they have liquid oceans
beneath their icy crust.

00:53:03.162 --> 00:53:04.620
And there's a really
high potential

00:53:04.620 --> 00:53:07.750
that they could have life--
probably not intelligent life,

00:53:07.750 --> 00:53:09.000
but there could be life there.

00:53:09.000 --> 00:53:11.390
And for me at the moment,
